NBA WESTERN CONFERENCE FINALS: SPURS v SUNS
May 29, 2005
Manu Ginobili
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT







<p>	Q.  People on TV are talking about -- do you feel like you are going to the wire?</p>
<p>	Q.  People are starting to talk about how exciting a player you are, how entertaining and how much they like you.  Are you the kind of player that has always had the coach telling you don't do that?</p>
<p>	Q.  What did you use to do?</p>
<p>	Q.  You remember the point where you, Tim (Duncan) and Tony (Parker) were all superstars, do you remember when it became that it wasn't just Tim and the rest of the guys but it was the three of you?</p>
<p>	Q.  Do you think the Olympics for you helped that image maybe across the league?</p>
<p>	Q.  You guys don't go into a series thinking sweep.  Would you have ever imagined being in this position being in the Western Conference Finals against the Suns?</p>
<p>	Q.  You talked about finding a balance between the kind of player you used to be.  Is Pop finding a balance too in terms of letting you go more than he used to?</p>
<p>	Q.  How much is getting -- you do like to get the crowd involved.  How much of that's just part of your game making you better?</p>
<p>	Q.  How old were you when you started to figure out you are not only a good player but you were a different player?</p>
<p>	Q.  Yes.  Were you really young?</p>
<p>	Q.  Are you faster than people?  Can you jump higher --</p>



